AD_Val_Rule.Name: ZZ_Woocommerce_Map_MProductOnBom
AD_Val_Rule.Code: m_product_Id IN (SELECT pbl.m_product_id FROM PP_Product_BOMLine pbl JOIN PP_Product_BOM ppb ON ppb.PP_Product_BOM_id = pbl.PP_Product_BOM_id AND ppb.bomtype = 'A' AND ppb.m_product_id=@M_Product_ID@ JOIN m_product mp ON mp.m_product_id = pbl.m_product_id JOIN bld_product_parttype bld ON bld.m_parttype_id = mp.m_parttype_id WHERE bld.bld_product_parttype_id = @BLD_Product_PartType_ID@)

AD_Column.Name: Comment/Help
AD_Column.Help: The Help field contains a hint, comment or help about the use of this item.

AD_Column.Name: Description
AD_Column.Description: Optional short description of the record
AD_Column.Help: A description is limited to 255 characters.

AD_Column.Name: Attribute Set Instance
AD_Column.Help: The values of the actual Product Attribute Instances. The product level attributes are defined on Product level.

AD_Val_Rule.Name: ZZ_Woocommerce_Map_MAttributes
AD_Val_Rule.Code: m_attribute.m_attribute_id IN(SELECT mau.m_attribute_id FROM m_attributeuse mau JOIN m_product mp ON mau.m_attributeset_id = mp.m_attributeset_id AND mp.m_product_id = @M_Product_ID@ JOIN m_attribute ma ON mau.m_attribute_id = ma.m_attribute_id AND ma.isinstanceattribute ='Y')

AD_Column.Name: Attribute
AD_Column.Help: Product Attribute like Color, Size

AD_Val_Rule.Name: ZZ_Woocommerce_Map_MAttributeValues
AD_Val_Rule.Code: m_attributevalue.m_attributevalue_id IN (SELECT mav.m_attributevalue_id FROM m_attributevalue mav WHERE mav.m_attribute_id = @M_Attribute_ID@)

AD_Column.Name: Attribute Value
AD_Column.Help: Individual value of a product attribute (e.g. green, large, ..)

AD_Val_Rule.Name: ZZ_Woocommerce_Map_MAttributes_Product
AD_Val_Rule.Code: m_attribute.m_attribute_id IN(SELECT mau.m_attribute_id FROM m_attributeuse mau JOIN m_product mp ON mau.m_attributeset_id = mp.m_attributeset_id AND mp.m_product_id =@M_Product_Line_ID@ JOIN m_attribute ma ON mau.m_attribute_id = ma.m_attribute_id AND ma.isinstanceattribute ='Y')

AD_Val_Rule.Name: ZZ_Woocommerce_Map_MAttributeValues_Product
AD_Val_Rule.Code: m_attributevalue.m_attributevalue_id IN (SELECT mav.m_attributevalue_id FROM m_attributevalue mav WHERE mav.m_attribute_id = @M_Attribute_Product_ID@)

AD_Column.Name: Add_To_Duplicate
AD_Column.Help: Setting this checkbox will do 2 things: It will tell the system to duplicate the current orderline being processed and also add the current record to the list of things to change in the duplicate record. This is typically used so that one order line in WooCommerce can create 2 orderlines in Idempiere. EG dual roller blinds, dual curtains.

AD_Field.Name: Add To Duplicate
AD_Field.Help: Setting this checkbox will do 2 things: It will tell the system to duplicate the current orderline being processed and also add the current record to the list of things to change in the duplicate record. This is typically used so that one order line in WooCommerce can create 2 orderlines in Idempiere. EG dual roller blinds, dual curtains.

AD_Field.Name: Active
AD_Field.Description: The record is active in the system
AD_Field.Help: There are two methods of making records unavailable in the system: One is to delete the record, the other is to de-activate the record. A de-activated record is not available for selection, but available for reports. There are two reasons for de-activating and not deleting records: (1) The system requires the record for audit purposes. (2) The record is referenced by other records. E.g., you cannot delete a Business Partner, if there are invoices for this partner record existing. You de-activate the Business Partner and prevent that this record is used for future entries.
